1/06eba37e-d307-11e2-b3a2-3bf5eb37b9d0_story.html |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130613062350/http://www.washingtonpost.com/sports/colleges/american-athletic-conference-picks-memphis-to-host-leagues-1st-mens-basketball-tournament/2013/06/11/06eba37e-d307-11e2-b3a2-3bf5eb37b9d0_story.html |archive-date=June 13, 2013 |newspaper=[[Washington Post]] | url-status=dead}}</ref> FedExForum had previously hosted eight [[Conference USA]] basketball tournaments.\n\nEven though the [[Big East Conference]] was meant to be a basketball-oriented conference, UConn, a member of The&nbsp;American, won the [[2014 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament]] (the first after the conferences split).\n\n===All-time school records by winning percentage===\nThis list goes through the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2019\u201320 season]].\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:1em auto; width:90%;\"<!-- NOTE: Final Fours includes all divisions, national championships includes pre-NCAA and AIAW -->\n|-\n! No. !! Team !! Records !! Win Pct.  !! The American<br />Tournament <br> Championships !!  The American <br /> Regular Season <br> Championships !! Final Fours !! National <br> Championships\n|-\n| 1 || [[Memphis Tigers men's basketball|Memphis]] || 1,336\u2013662 || {{winpct|1336|662}} || 0 || 0 || 3 || 0\n|-\n| 2 || [[Cincinnati Bearcats men's basketball|Cincinnati]] || 1,835\u20131026 || {{winpct|1835|1026}} || 2 || 3 || 6 || 2\n|-\n| 3 || [[Temple Owls men's basketball|Temple]] || 1,940\u20131,096 || {{winpct|1940|1096}} || 0 || 1 || 2 || 1\n|-\n| 4 || [[Houston Cougars men's basketball|Houston]] || 1,247\u2013823 || {{winpct|1247|823}} || 0 || 2 || 5 || 0\n|-\n| 5 || [[Wichita State Shockers men's basketball|Wichita State]] || 1,609\u20131,211 || {{winpct|1609|1211}} || 0 || 0 || 2 || 0\n|-\n| 6 || [[Tulsa Golden Hurricane men's basketball|Tulsa]] || 1,471\u20131,168 || {{winpct|1471|1168}} || 0 || 1 || 0 || 0\n|-\n| 7 |