er being eliminated from the conference tournament, went on to become the national champions after beating [[2013\u201314 Kentucky Wildcats men's basketball team|Kentucky]] 60\u201354 in [[2014 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Championship Game|the title game]].}}\n| ''[[2013\u201314 Louisville Cardinals men's basketball team|Louisville]]''{{efn|group=mbcc|After Louisville basketball staffer [[Andre McGee]] was found to have paid a local [[Procuring (prostitution)|madam]] to [[2015 University of Louisville basketball sex scandal|provide strippers and prostitutes]] to players and recruits from 2010 through 2014, the NCAA ordered all Louisville records from the 2010\u201311 through 2013\u201314 seasons to be vacated.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espn.com/mens-college-basketball/story/_/id/22513517/ncaa-denies-louisville-appeal-rules-cardinals-vacate-2013-national-title |title=NCAA denies Louisville's appeal, rules Cardinals must vacate 2013 national title |first=Mark |last=Schlabach |authorlink=Mark Schlabach |website=ESPN.com |date=February 20, 2017 |accessdate=February 20, 2017}}</ref>}}\n| ''31\u20136 (15\u20133)''\n| ''#5''\n| ''#9''\n| ''[[2014 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Sweet Sixteen]]''\n| rowspan=2 | ''Louisville''\n| rowspan=2 | ''31\u20136''\n| rowspan=2 | ''#5''\n| rowspan=2 | ''#9''\n| rowspan=2 | ''NCAA Sweet Sixteen''\n|-\n| [[2013\u201314 Cincinnati Bearcats men's basketball team|Cincinnati]]\n| 27\u20137 (15\u20133)\n| #15\n| #22\n| [[2014 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Second Round]]\n|-\n| [[2014\u201315 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|2014\u201315]]\n| [[2014-15 SMU Mustangs men's basketball team|SMU]]\n| 27\u20137 (15\u20133)\n| #18\n| RV\n| [[2015 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA First Round]]\n| SMU\n| 27\u20137\n| #18\n| RV\n| NCAA First Round\n|-\n| [[2015\u201316 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|2015\u201316]]\n| [[2015\u201316 Temple Owls men's 