[[Association of American Universities]]|accessdate=June 6, 2014}}</ref> Seven members are doctorate-granting universities with \"very high research activity,\" the highest classification given by the [[Carnegie Foundation for the Advancement of Teaching]].<ref name=\"carnegie\">{{cite web|url=http://carnegieclassifications.iu.edu/resources/ |title=Carnegie Classifications Institution Lookup |publisher=[[Carnegie Foundation for the Advancement of Teaching]] |year=2014 |accessdate=April 30, 2015}}</ref> Member schools are also highly ranked nationally and globally by various groups, including ''[[U.S. News & World Report]]'', ''[[Washington Monthly]]'', and ''[[Times Higher Education World University Rankings|Times Higher Education]]''.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center; margin:1em auto; font-size:95%;\"\n|-\n! University\n! Location\n! Affiliation\n! [[Carnegie Classification of Institutions of Higher Education|Carnegie]]<ref name=\"carnegie\"/>\n! [[Financial endowment|Endowment]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nacubo.org/Documents/EndowmentFiles/2014_Endowment_Market_Values_Revised.pdf |title=National Association of College and University Business Officers |publisher=National Association of College and University Business |year=2014 |accessdate=April 30, 2015 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170223091003/http://www.nacubo.org/Documents/EndowmentFiles/2014_Endowment_Market_Values_Revised.pdf |archive-date=February 23, 2017 |url-status=dead |df=mdy-all }}</ref>\n! [[U.S. News and World Report#America's Best Colleges|''USN'' Nat.]]<ref name=\"US News Rankings\">{{cite web |url=http://colleges.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-colleges/rankings/national-universities |title=Best College Rankings and Lists |year=2016 |website=[[U.S. News & World Report]] |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110521210513/http://colleges.usnews.rankingsandreviews.com/best-colleges/rankings/national-universities |archive-date=May 21, 2011 |url-status=dead |access-date=July 15, 2018}}</ref>\n! [[Washington Monthly college rankings|''WM'' Nat.]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://washingtonmonthly.com/college_guide?ranking=2016-rankings-national-universities |title=Washington Monthly College Guide 2016 National Universities |work=[[Washington Monthly]] |year=2016 |accessdate=June 30, 2017}}</ref>\n! [[University Ranking by Academic Performance|URAP U.S.]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.urapcenter.org/2016/country.php?ccode=US&rank=all |title=University Ranking by Academic Performance \u2013 United States of America 2016\u20132017 |publisher=Informatics Institute, Middle East Technical University |year=2017 |accessdate=June 30, 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n! {{sort|Central Florida|[[University of Central Florida]]}}\n| [[Orlando, Florida]]\n| [[Public university|Public]] ([[State University System of Florida|SUSF]])\n| Research (VH)\n| $135,500,000\n| 176\n| 211\n| 114\n|-\n! {{sort|Cincinnati|[[University of Cincinnati]]}}\n| [[Cincinnati|Cincinnati, Ohio]]\n| Public ([[University System of Ohio|USO]])\n| Research (VH)\n| $1,183,922,000\n| 135\n| 191\n| 57\n|-\n! [[East Carolina University]]\n| [[Greenville, North Carolina]]\n| Public ([[University of North Carolina|UNC]])\n| Doctoral\n| $164,065,000\n| 210\n| 171\n| 69\n|-\n! {{sort|Houston|[[University of Houston]]}}\n| [[Houston|Houston, Texas]]\n| Public ([[University of Houston System|UH&nbsp;System]])\n| Research (VH)\n| $789,700,000\n| 194\n| 68\n| 104\n|-\n! {{sort|Memphis|[[University of Memphis]]}}\n| [[Memphis, Tennessee]]\n| Public ([[Tennessee Board of Regents|TBR]])\n| Research (H)\n| $200,750,000\n| RNP\n| 37\n| 188\n|-\n! {{sort|South Florida|[[University of South Florida]]}}\n| [[Tampa, Florida]]\n| Public ([[State University System of Florida|SUSF]])\n| Research (VH)\n| $447,000,000\n| 159\n| 78\n| 72\n|-\n! [[Southern Methodist University]]\n| [[University Park, Texas]]\n| [[Private university|Private]] ([[United Methodist Church|Methodist]])\n| Research (H)\n