mbers \u2013 in 13 states, including California, Connecticut, Florida, Kansas, Louisiana, Maryland, North Carolina, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, Tennessee, Texas, and Virginia. The newest full member, Wichita State, is the only one that [[List of NCAA Division I non-football programs|does not sponsor football]].\n\n===Current members===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n!Institution !! Location !! Founded !! Joined !! Type !! Enrollment !! Nickname !!class=\"unsortable\"|Colors\n|-\n!{{sort|Central Florida|[[University of Central Florida]]}} (UCF)\n|[[Orlando, Florida]]\n|1963\n|2013\n|Public\n|68,571<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.ucf.edu/about-ucf/facts/|title=UCF Facts 2017-2018 - University of Central Florida - Orlando, FL|publisher=|accessdate=July 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|[[UCF Knights|Knights]]\n|{{college color boxes|UCF Knights}}\n|-\n!{{sort|Cincinnati|[[University of Cincinnati]]}}\n|[[Cincinnati|Cincinnati, Ohio]]\n|1819\n|2013\n|Public\n|45,949<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uc.edu/about/ucfactsheet.html|title=UC Facts|website=University of Cincinnati|accessdate=July 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|[[Cincinnati Bearcats|Bearcats]]\n|{{college color boxes|Cincinnati Bearcats}}\n|-\n![[East Carolina University]]\n|[[Greenville, North Carolina]]\n|1907\n|2014\n|Public\n|28,718<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ecu.edu/cs-admin/news/Record-Enrollment.cfm|title=Record Enrollment|website=www.ecu.edu|accessdate=July 15, 2018}}</ref>\n|[[East Carolina Pirates|Pirates]]\n|{{college color boxes|East Carolina Pirates}}\n|-\n!{{sort|Houston|[[University of Houston]]}}\n|[[Houston|Houston, Texas]]\n|1927\n|2013\n|Public\n|46,324<ref>https://www.uh.edu/ir/reports/facts-at-a-glance/facts-at-a-glance.pdf</ref>\n|[[Houston Cougars|Cougars]]\n|{{college color boxes|Houston Cougars}}\n|-\n!{{sort|Memphis|[[University of Memphis]]}}\n|[[Memphis, Tennessee]]\n|1912\n|2013\n|Public\n|21,458<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.memphis.edu/about/facts.php|title=UofM Facts 