18 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|2017\u201318]]\n| [[2017\u201318 Cincinnati Bearcats men's basketball team|Cincinnati]]\n| 30\u20134 (16\u20132)\n| #6\n| #6\n| [[2018 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Second Round]]\n| Cincinnati\n| 30\u20134\n| #6\n| #8\n| NCAA Second Round\n|-\n| [[2018\u201319 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|2018\u201319]]\n| [[2018\u201319 Houston Cougars men's basketball team|Houston]]\n| 33\u20133(16\u20132)\n| #9\n| #11\n| [[2019 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Sweet Sixteen]]\n| [[2018\u201319 Cincinnati Bearcats men's basketball team|Cincinnati]]\n| 28\u20137\n| #22\n| #24\n| NCAA First Round\n|-\n| rowspan=3 |[[2019\u201320 American Athletic Conference men's basketball season|2019\u201320]]\n| [[2019\u201320 Cincinnati Bearcats men's basketball team|Cincinnati]]\n| 20\u201310(15\u20133)\n| NR\n| NR\n| rowspan=3 |Cancelled{{efn|group=mbcc|[[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament]] was cancelled due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|Coronavirus Pandemic]]}}\n|colspan=5, rowspan=3 | Cancelled{{efn|group=mbcc|[[2020 American Athletic Conference Men's Basketball Tournament]] was cancelled due to the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|Coronavirus Pandemic]]}}\n|-\n| [[2019\u201320 Houston Cougars men's basketball team|Houston]]\n| 27\u20137 (15\u20133)\n| #22\n| #23\n|-\n| [[2019\u201320 Tulsa Golden Hurricane men's basketball team|Tulsa]]\n| 21\u201310 (15\u20133)\n| NR\n| NR\n|-\n|}\n\n{{notelist|group=mbcc}}\n\n===Rivalries===\nThe American has many rivalries among its member schools, some of which existed before the conference was established. Recent conference realignment in 2005 and 2013 ended \u2013 or temporarily halted \u2013 many rivalries. Before their departure to other conferences, a number of former member schools held longtime rivalries within the conference.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"  style=\"text-align:center; width:95%;\"\n|-\n! Teams !! Rivalry Name !! Meetings !! Began !! Record !! Series leader !! Current Streak\n|-\n| [[Cincinnati\u2013Memphis rivalry#Men's Basketball|Cincinnati\u2013Memphis]] || \u2014 || 81 || 1968 || 47\u201333 || Cincinnati || Cincinnati won 1\n|-\n| [[South Florida\u2013UCF rivalry#Men's basketball|South Florida\u2013UCF]] || War on I\u20134 || 39 || 1972 || 23\u201318|| South Florida || South Florida won 1\n|-\n| [[Houston\u2013SMU rivalry#Men's Basketball|Houston\u2013SMU]] || \u2014 || 86 || 1956 || 53\u201333|| Houston || SMU won 1\n|-\n| [[Tulsa\u2013Wichita State men's basketball rivalry|Tulsa\u2013Wichita State]] || \u2014 || 132 || 1931 ||  70\u201362 || Wichita || Wichita won 1\n|}\n''Results as of the [[2019\u201320 NCAA Division I men's basketball season|2019\u201320 season]].''\n\n==Women's basketball==\n{{See also|American Athletic Conference Women's Basketball Tournament}}\nIn June 2013, it was announced that the inaugural women's basketball tournament would take place at the [[Mohegan Sun]] in [[Connecticut]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AAC tournament host site picked |url=http://espn.go.com/womens-college-basketball/story/_/id/9360692/mohegan-sun-host-first-american-athletic-conference-tourney |publisher=[[ESPN]] |accessdate=June 30, 2014}}</ref> Women's basketball teams have played a total of 20 times in the [[NCAA Women's Division I Basketball Championship]] (since 1982), with [[UConn Huskies women's basketball|UConn]] winning 11 national championships under head coach [[Geno Auriemma]] since 1995. Women's national championship tournaments prior to 1982 were run by the [[AIAW Women's Basketball Tournament|AIAW]].\n\n===All-time school records by winning percentage===\nThis list goes through the 2016\u201317 season.<ref>{{cite web|title=NCAA Division I Women's Basketball Records Through 2012\u201313|url=http://fs.ncaa.org/Docs/stats/w_basketball_RB/2014/DI.pdf|publisher=[[NCAA]]|accessdate=March 18, 2014}}</ref>\n\n{| cla